Distribution and habitat:
Tropidolaemus laticinctus
is so far known only from the Indonesian Provinces of Sulawesi Utara and Sulawesi Tengah in northern Sulawesi island (fig. 12 ). Available information on collecting localities place this species in lowland to lower montane rainforest. The vertical distribution of the new species extends from near sea level (Paleleh) and about 100 m (Matinan Mts.) to at least 550 m above sea level ( 1800 feet , at Sonder, Sulawesi Utara;
Boulenger [ 1897 ]
). A specimen in Dumoga Bone National Park (Sulawesi Utara) was observed close to a small river (T. Ahnby, personal communication; fig. 11 A+B).
